  "properties": {
    "type": "USql",
    "script": "
DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS testdb14212; CREATE DATABASE testdb14212; 
//Create Table
CREATE TABLE testdb14212.dbo.testtbl11652
(
        //Define schema of table
        UserId          int, 
        Start           DateTime, 
        Region          string, 
        Query           string, 
        Duration        int, 
        Urls            string, 
        ClickedUrls     string,
    INDEX idx1 //Name of index
    CLUSTERED (Region ASC) //Column to cluster by
    PARTITIONED BY BUCKETS (UserId) HASH (Region) //Column to partition by
);

ALTER TABLE testdb14212.dbo.testtbl11652 ADD IF NOT EXISTS PARTITION (1);

DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS testdb14212.dbo.testtvf12932;

//create table weblogs on space-delimited website log data
CREATE FUNCTION testdb14212.dbo.testtvf12932()
RETURNS @result TABLE
(
    s_date DateTime,
    s_time string,
    s_sitename string,
    cs_method string, 
    cs_uristem string,
    cs_uriquery string,
    s_port int,
    cs_username string, 
    c_ip string,
    cs_useragent string,
    cs_cookie string,
    cs_referer string, 
    cs_host string,
    sc_status int,
    sc_substatus int,
    sc_win32status int, 
    sc_bytes int,
    cs_bytes int,
    s_timetaken int
)
AS
BEGIN

    @result = EXTRACT
        s_date DateTime,
        s_time string,
        s_sitename string,
        cs_method string,
        cs_uristem string,
        cs_uriquery string,
        s_port int,
        cs_username string,
        c_ip string,
        cs_useragent string,
        cs_cookie string,
        cs_referer string,
        cs_host string,
        sc_status int,
        sc_substatus int,
        sc_win32status int,
        sc_bytes int,
        cs_bytes int,
        s_timetaken int
    FROM @"/Samples/Data/WebLog.log"
    USING Extractors.Text(delimiter:' ');

RETURN;
END;
CREATE VIEW testdb14212.dbo.testview11011 
AS 
    SELECT * FROM 
    (
        VALUES(1,2),(2,4)
    ) 
AS 
T(a, b);
CREATE PROCEDURE testdb14212.dbo.testproc19998()
AS BEGIN
  CREATE VIEW testdb14212.dbo.testview11011 
  AS 
    SELECT * FROM 
    (
        VALUES(1,2),(2,4)
    ) 
  AS 
  T(a, b);
END;"
  }
}
